From poverty-stricken communities who resort to subsistence poaching to fill empty stomachs to organised gangs armed with AK47s seeking ivory to fun<span class="text_exposed_show">d terrorist activities, is it really possible to lump all poachers into one bag and apply an extreme blanket policy to all? And, by shooting a poacher dead, have you just lost your most important source of information?</span>

